<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="489" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,1564,1949]" pageId="10" pageNumber="489">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1815,1840]" pageId="10" pageNumber="489">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species is a challenging taxon and needs a thorough taxonomic revision. Our specimens exhibited three color patterns and marked variation in minor chela morphology. According to 
<bibRefCitation author="Anker, A. &amp; De Grave, S." pageId="10" pageNumber="489" pagination="343 - 454" refId="ref11825" refString="Anker, A. &amp; De Grave, S. (2016) An updated and annotated checklist of marine and brackish caridean shrimps of Singapore (Crustacea, Decapoda). Raffles Bulletin of Zoology, 34, 343 - 454." type="journal article" year="2016">Anker &amp; De Grave (2016)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dana" authorityYear="1852" box="[243,379,1888,1912]" class="Malacostraca" family="Alpheidae" genus="Alpheus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="10" pageNumber="489" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pacificus">
<emphasis box="[243,379,1888,1912]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="489">A. pacificus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is composed of three genetically well-defined clades, each most likely corresponding to a distinct species. Most likely, molecular tools will be needed to clarify the status of our material.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
